    • Method Detail

      • preInvokeOperation

        public boolean preInvokeOperation(java.lang.String operationName,
                                  java.lang.Object... args)
        This method is called before invoking service operations. Argument operationName have the value of the operation which is going to invoke. If this method returns true then that service operation will be invoked. If this method returns false then no operation will be invoked and a null value will be returned.
        Parameters:
        operationName - the operation name
        args - the parameters for this operation
        Returns:
        if true continue to execute the operation, otherwise stop

      • postInvokeOperation

        public java.lang.Object postInvokeOperation(java.lang.String operationName,
                                            java.lang.Object result,
                                            java.lang.Object... args)
        This method will be called after invoking a service operation. Argument operationName has the value of the operation which was invoked. and argument result has the value which is returned by invoking the operation.
        Parameters:
        operationName - the operation name
        result - the result after executing the operation
        args - the parameters for this operation
        Returns:
        object to be returned to requester
